Graham Keegan hedges her endorsement as conditional.The condition:
creating a database on students. For five years, Keegan has pressed
for a statewide computer accounting system to track school
enrollment, dropouts and achievement. She believes the system will
better show where the billions of dollars that Arizona spends on
education goes, and whether it is properly applied. By ROBBIE
