   TORSO08 (Scottsdale, Ariz.) _ When investigators examined the
smooth, straight cuts left on a torso found in a trash bin in
January, they thought somebody must have used a powerful electrical
saw to dismember the man's body. So detectives searched Ira
Pomerantz's bar, trying to find what they initially figured was a
meat-cutting instrument. Although they found nothing there, they
did find evidence in his wife's purse that she bought a
reciprocating saw late last year, according to a source close to
the investigation. By CHRISTINA LEONARD and BETH DEFALCO. Story
will move in the ``A'' category.
