<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Portable DVD is just grand _ actually, $1,300
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   If you love your DVD collection and can't stand to be without
your movies when you travel, the Sharp DV-L70U ($1,300,
www.sharp-usa.com) is an excellent way to view them in style. With
a 7-inch LCD display that produces clear, vibrant images on an
anti-glare screen and good sound, the DV-L70U will play DVDs, Video
CDs and standard audio CDs. It has inputs and outputs for
displaying from other sources or outputting to your home system
with digital sound if you want to use it as a standard DVD player.
Boasting a battery life of about three hours on a single charge,
the portable player lives up to its main purpose: With headphones,
it's the ultimate in-flight gadget. But with the cost of standard
DVD players dipping below $200, the price just doesn't seem right.
Still, if DVDs are your game, the Sharp portable DVD player is a
phenomenal product and a great way to organize your own personal
screening.
</P>
