<HEADLINE>
SOMETHING ELSE DISTURBING ABOUT `AMERICAN BEAUTY' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``American Beauty'' _ I know it dominated the
Oscars with Best Picture, Best Actor, Best Practically Everything
but there's something disturbing about this comic indictment of
American middle class morality. And it's not the theme. David
Lynch's ``Blue Velvet,'' which deals with some of the same sexual
darkness, was deeper and darker and funnier. It's the attitude
that's akew. I may be wrong about this but the whole tone of the
movie was patronizing toward the characters and condescending to
the audience. It's as if a bunch of Hollywood insiders decided to
take a few broad pot shots at middle America and couldn't contain
their giggling superiority.
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: Fans of Sherlock Holmes can rejoice with the release
on Tuesday of ``An Evening With Sherlock Holmes.'' Actually, it
should be titled several evenings because this boxed set contains
four movies _ ``Sherlock Holmes and the Secret Weapon'' (1942),
``Woman In Green'' (1945), ``Terror By Night'' (1946) and ``Dressed
To Kill'' (1946). And that's not all. It also includes an interview
with Holmes creator Sir Arthur Conan Doyle filmed in 1927 and 30
original radio broadcasts starring the film's leads, Basil Rathbone
and Nigel Bruce. The complete set is available for a retail price
of $69.95.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 16: ``The World Is Not Enough'' (DVD),
``Dreaming of Joseph Lees,'' ``Felicia's Journey,'' ``The End of
the Affair,'' ``The Straight Story,'' ``The Cradle Will Rock.'' May
23: ``Sleepy Hollow,'' ``Escape From Mars,'' ``Train of Life,''
``American Movie,'' ``Comic Book Confidential,'' ``Eye of the
Beholder,'' ``Laserhawk,'' ``Love and Action in Chicago,'' ``The
Source.'' May 30: ``Snow Falling on Cedars'' (DVD), ``Miss Julie,''
``Man on the Moon'' (DVD), ``Divided We Stand,'' ``The 20th
Century'' (10 vol.) (DVD). June 6: ``Girl, Interrupted''(DVD),
``Mr. Death: The Rise and Fall of Fred A. Leuchter, Jr.'' (DVD),
``Backlash,'' ``Kiss the Sky'' (DVD), ``A Scandal in Paris,'' ``On
Our Merry Way'' (DVD), ``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.'' June
13: ``Leila'' (DVD), ``The Emperor and the Assassin'' (DVD),
``Desperately Seeking Susan'' (DVD), ``The Third Miracle'' (DVD),
``Light It Up.''
</P>
</TEXT>
