   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH - Texas Gov. George W. Bush works on improving relations
with a group and a man who could prove pivotal to his presidential
ambitions. Three months after insulting some Catholics by speaking
at Bob Jones University, Bush on Monday re-arranged his schedule so
he could attend Cardinal O'Connor's funeral. On Tuesday, he meets
with former foe John McCain. (Herman, Austin American-Statesman).
20-25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-VOTERS _ Conventional wisdom pegs apathy as the leading
cause of dismal turnout among potential voters between the ages of
18 and 34, but some election experts and activists say the problem
is deeper than that. From obstinate election officials to
registration laws that don't take into account the mobility of the
young, the U.S. electoral system offers more obstacles than
incentives, say advocates who are trying to reverse the decline in
participation among young Americans. (Dayton Daily News).
</P>
