<P>
   Sports stories from The New York Times News Service for
 &UR; TUESDAY &LR; , May 9.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-ANDERSON-COLUMN (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ Sports of The
Times on the Devils-Leafs, Game 6. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-DEVILS-LEAFS (East Rutherford, N.J.) _ N.J. Devils, Toronto
Maple Leafs, Game 6, 7 p.m. EDT start. The Devils hold a 3-2 edge
in the best-of-seven series. By Alex Yannis.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ARATON-COLUMN (Miami) _ Sports of The Times column on the
Knicks, who now actually find themselves in a familiar, and
somewhat comfortable, position now that they trail Miami, 1 game to
none, in their Eastern Conference playoff series. By Harvey Araton.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-RAYS (New York) _ Tampa Bay at the Yankees, 7:05 p.m.
By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-PROTEST (Sydney, Australia) _ Noisy critics of aspects of
the Sydney Olympics kicked sand in the eyes of the Games organizers
in a beach protest staged to attract TV coverage and force
concessions. The demonstrators won network news play here and
elsewhere, but no retreat yet by officials from a decision to stage
Olympic volleyball at Bondi Beach.
</P>
