A9083 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w BC-MOMS-GOALS09-COX     05-08 0195
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOMS-GOALS09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With MOMS-MARCH.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   GOALS OF THE MILLION MOM MARCH
</P>
<P>
   _ Sensible ``cooling-off'' periods and background checks for
anyone who wants to purchase, from any person or place, weapons
capable of killing or injuring people.
</P>
<P>
   _ Requiring handgun owners to be licensed and all handguns to be
registered.
</P>
<P>
   _ Requiring manufacturers to build in safety locks for all
handguns.
</P>
<P>
   _ Limiting an individual's purchases of handguns to one per
month.
</P>
<P>
   _ Strict enforcement of existing gun laws at all levels.
</P>
<P>
   _ Enlistment of corporate America in spreading the message that
``guns _ in the wrong hands _ are simply unacceptable.'' These
``child-friendly'' companies should offer goods that law
enforcement agencies can in turn offer in exchange for guns. The
guns that are turned in would be destroyed.
</P>
<P>
   _ Recruitment of mothers, grandmothers, stepmothers, godmothers,
future mothers and all others willing to be ``honorary mothers'' to
join a continuing crusade for sensible gun control laws.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
