<HEADLINE>
DON'T BE A MULE: LEARN TO LUG LESS
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies ART OF PACKING) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Container Store offers free workshops on organizing your
trips.
</P>
<P>
   For locations, call (800) 786-7315.
</P>
<P>
   Anne McAlpin _ the woman Oprah turned to for packing advice _
has a book and video series, Pack It Up, covering packing advice,
travel wardrobe planning, security and safety tips, and
accessorizing ideas. She also holds packing seminars around the
nation and appears regularly on House and Garden TV. For more
information, call (800) 977-PACK or visit www.packitup.com.
</P>
<P>
   On the Internet, try The Compleat Carry-On Traveler
(www.oratory.com/travel), which offers thoughtful and useful advice
on traveling in general and packing in particular, including an
exhaustive packing list. Also helpful is the Universal Packing List
(www.henricson.se/mats/upl). This site consists of a number of
packing lists, from basics like clothing, health care and travel
documents, to packing for specialized activities, such as diving
and mountain climbing.
</P>
<P>
   _ Patricia Rodriguez
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
