<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of May
9 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Patrick Hipes at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BKN-SUNS-SKILES (Los Angeles) _ Scott Skiles is the youngest coach
in the NBA at 36, but has done well in keeping the Phoenix Suns on
track in the playoffs despite the team's tumultuous season. As for
the second-round playoff matchup with the Los Angeles Lakers,
Skiles also has added insight on a certain Lakers center, a former
teammate in Orlando. 
By Steve Dilbeck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Phoenix Suns forward Rodney
Rogers won the NBA's Sixth Man award this season, the latest case
of an ex-Los Angeles Clipper doing well for another team. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BKN-LAKERS-NOTEBOOK (Los Angeles) _ A daily Los Angeles Lakers
playoff notebook. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS-DIAMONDBACKS (Phoenix) _ The Los Angeles Dodgers face
the Arizona Diamondbacks at Bank One Ballpark. 6:35 p.m. PDT. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS-NOTEBOOK (Phoenix) _ A daily Los Angeles Dodgers
notebook. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBA-A'S-ANGELS (Anaheim, Calif.) _ The Anaheim Angels face the
Oakland A's at Edison Field. 7:05 p.m. PDT. 
By Billy Witz/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
BBA-ANGELS-NOTEBOOK (Anaheim, Calif.) _ A daily Anaheim Angels
notebook. 
By Billy Witz/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 

