<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `American Beauty' released for video rental
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Oscar winner for best picture, ``American Beauty,'' debuts
today on video, but it's priced for renting, not buying.
</P>
<P>
   The movie, which won five Academy Awards, including best actor
(Kevin Spacey) and best screenplay (Alan Ball), carries a hefty
list price of $106.99. Some Web sites, including www.reel.com, are
selling it for $90.99.
</P>
<P>
   Internet users can pre-order used ``Beauty'' videos, expected to
be available July 28, for $9.99 at
www.reel.com/movie.asp?MID &QC; 127744.
</P>
<P>
   The movie is expected to be released on DVD in September.
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
