<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    ORGAN DONATION BY THE NUMBERS
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The number of organs or portions of organs donated by living
donors has increased considerably over the past 10 years. The
number of organs donated by living donors and those donated by
people in death:
</P>
<P>
   ORGAN 1989 1999
</P>
<P>
   Living donor/cadaver Living donor/cadaver
</P>
<P>
   Kidney 1,903/6,754 4,432/8,097
</P>
<P>
   Kidney-pancreas 0/334 3/1,185
</P>
<P>
   Pancreas 4/79 0/368
</P>
<P>
   Liver 2/2,199 173/4,527
</P>
<P>
   Intestine 0/0 0/71
</P>
<P>
   Heart 9/1,696 5/2,180
</P>
<P>
   Lung 0/93 14/887
</P>
<P>
   Heart-lung 0/67 0/48
</P>
<P>
   Totals 1,918/11,222 4,627/17,363
</P>
<P>
   A living donor may give a single kidney, a lobe of a lung or
part of a liver or pancreas. A heart can be donated from a living
donor when that donor is receiving a heart-lung transplant;
sometimes surgeons decide it's best to transplant a heart and lungs
together if a patient needs a new set of lungs, and the heart-lung
patient's heart may be healthy enough to pass on to a patient
needing a new heart.
</P>
<P>
   Only 5,812 people who died last year had agreed to be organ
donors, but their donations helped 17,363 recipients.
</P>
<P>
   Transplant need
</P>
<P>
   Numbers of people in Georgia and the United States on the
registry awaiting transplants, as of April 30:
</P>
<P>
   Organ Nationwide Georgia
</P>
<P>
   Kidney 44,989 695
</P>
<P>
   Liver 15,185 75
</P>
<P>
   Pancreas 908 0
</P>
<P>
   Pancreas islet cells 155 0
</P>
<P>
   Kidney-pancreas 2,273 25
</P>
<P>
   Intestine 118 0
</P>
<P>
   Heart 4,131 91
</P>
<P>
   Heart-lung 210 1
</P>
<P>
   Lung 3,599 26
</P>
<P>
   Totals 69,227 913
</P>
<P>
   Donor lack
</P>
<P>
   The number of patients who died while awaiting organs in 1999:
</P>
<P>
   Kidney 2,969
</P>
<P>
   Kidney-pancreas 167
</P>
<P>
   Pancreas 17
</P>
<P>
   Pancreas islets 5
</P>
<P>
   Intestine 42
</P>
<P>
   Liver 1,733
</P>
<P>
   Heart 706
</P>
<P>
   Lung 578
</P>
<P>
   Heart-lung 53
</P>
<P>
   Total 6,012
</P>
<P>
   Source: United Network for Organ Sharing registry data as of
April 2000
</P>
