r l BC-ORGAN-WEB09-COX     05-08 0382
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ORGAN-WEB09-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    HOW TO BECOME A DONOR
 &HT;    By Patricia Guthrie
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The first step to becoming an organ donor in death is to sign an
organ donor card or change your driver's license to indicate your
wish to donate organs.
</P>
<P>
   The second step is as important: Notify your family of your
wishes. Your next-of-kin must consent to the donation if you die or
are brain-dead.
</P>
<P>
   It's also a good idea to tell your family physician, your
religious leader and your attorney.
</P>
<P>
   To request a donor card or more information on living or
cadaveric organ donation, contact LifeLink of Georgia, 3715
Northside Parkway, 100 Northcreek Suite 300, Atlanta, GA 30327 or
call 404-266-8884 or 1-800-544-6667 or
www.lifelinkfound.org/georgia/ga.html. The designation can be
changed on your driver's license when you renew it.
</P>
<P>
   People also can donate their whole body to medical research. But
in that case, organs can't be removed for transplantation. Contact
Medical College of Georgia in Augusta, 1-706-721-3731; Emory
University School of Medicine, 404-727-6242 (Morehouse School of
Medicine is affiliated with the Emory donor program.); Mercer
University School of Medicine, 1-912-301-2529 or Life College
School of Chiropractic, 770-426-2718.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE WEB
</P>
<P>
   Other Web sites for information on donation:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.livertransplant.org/
</P>
<P>
   The University of Southern California Liver Tranplant Program,
explains how Friday's transplant will be done.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.unos.org/
</P>
<P>
   United Network for Organ Sharing has latest organ waiting list
statistics, other information.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  http//Picasso.eushc.org/transplant/homepage.cgi
</P>
<P>
   Emory University Transplant Center's homepage, with information
on living donor kidney transplants and information on how to become
an organ donor in death.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.shareyourlife.org
</P>
<P>
   The Coalition on Donation to sign up for organ donation.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.transweb.org/
</P>
<P>
   General information on transplants and becoming a donor.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  www.a-s-t.org/ American Society of Transplantation
</P>
<P>
   Look up abstracts on scientific papers covering many aspects on
organ transplants.
</P>
<P>
   Patricia Guthrie writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
