   &UR; TECH21 (COLUMN)_ &LR;  Not counting the answering machine, the VCR and
the burglar alarm, there have been three technological revolutions
in my household over the past two decades. The first, of course,
was getting a computer at home. The second was instant access to
the Internet _ originally with ISDN, now with DSL. (The latter is
much faster, of course, but it was the former that brought about
