 &UR; WEBBY _ &LR;  For some Internet company executives, winning a Webby is
like winning an Academy Award. It means giving an acceptance speech
before a large crowd and wallowing in compliments from their peers
at the party afterward. But the parallel between being voted
pre-eminent on the Internet and best in film stops there,
especially where it counts the most in business: money. Unlike
movies, Internet sites that win industry acknowledgment usually get
only a modest reward, such as a temporary increase in visitors and
a few more advertisers.  &UR; BY VERNE KOPYTOFF &LR;
