 PERSONALS: The Pursuit of Happiness  
 (Eds: For release Monday, May 8. This story also moved in the 
 ``a'' national news file.)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   What's it like to use sexual energy to achieve higher
consciousness? ``We're the ultimate Tantric couple,'' says
 &UR; Oceana &LR; , in an interview with the Australian magazine Good Weekend.
``We're very passionate with each other: Our sexual chemistry is
mesmerizing.  &UR; Icarus &LR;  is very romantic. ... He's very supportive.
I'm a bit on the health-nut side. Just recently, I did a 10-day
juice fast. And he would never choose to do that, but he did it
with me. And he hates washing the juicer.''
</P>
<P>
   _ What's it like to be  &UR; Pete Townshend &LR; ? ``I always wanted there
to be a kind of  &UR; Paul Newman &LR;  and  &UR; Joanne Woodward &LR;  story,'' he
told Rolling Stone magazine, ``but they're one of the great
exceptions. I did hold  &UR; Paul McCartney &LR;  in high esteem because of
the way that he conducted his relationship. I have those kind of
old-fashioned family values. And that has infuriated, to the point
of hysteria, certain American rock critics and musicians, who think
that once you've thrown a TV through a hotel-room window, that's
you for life.''
</P>
<P>
   _ What's it like to live with  &UR; Kim Basinger &LR; ? ``Her emotions are
endlessly volatile,'' says a Vanity Fair profile forwarded by
 &UR; Mark Sloan &LR; . Sometimes  &UR; Alec Baldwin &LR; , her husband, will awake to
find her ``sitting with a fist in her mouth and a look of horror on
her face, tears streaming down her cheeks as she watches the
television news: `Alec, we've just got to do something about the
Albanian refugees!'''
</P>
<P>
   _ What's it like to visit the Hoosiers?  &UR; Roberto Gonzalez &LR; , just
back from Indiana, saw side-by-side billboards in Muncie: (Left)
``I will wait for sex!'' (Right) ``Enjoy Indiana.com.''
</P>
<P>
   _ What's it like to date a millionaire? This month's Elle
magazine follows in the footsteps of last month's Harper's Bazaar,
with a story that could be right out of  &UR; Peter Arno &LR; 's '30s
cartoons on gold-digging chorus girls. In 2000, the marks aren't
elderly businessmen in suits; they're young dot-commers with bank
accounts.  &UR; Deanna Kizis &LR; , who dated five new millionaires,
concluded that they are all geeky, techno-spouting and
self-absorbed. Is this different from stereotyping women as bimbos?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &QL;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ San Francisco Giants manager  &UR; Dusty Baker &LR;  is chairing a
campaign to raise money to house formerly homeless veterans in the
Presidio. The Campaign for the Veterans Academy Endowment,
organized by Swords to Plowshares, is hoping to raise $5 million
for the project, which will provide housing, education and jobs.
</P>
<P>
   _ A US Weekly poll found that 23 percent of Americans want
 &UR; Cybill Shepherd &LR;  to replace  &UR; Kathy Lee Gifford &LR;  as  &UR; Regis &LR; 
 &UR; Philbin &LR; 's partner; and 22 percent want  &UR; Joan Lunden &LR; . Gifford
herself likes  &UR; Jerry Seinfeld &LR;  for the job.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Keith Wall &LR;  is puzzling over the sign posted by the
Burlingame, Calif., Planning Commission on a property in that town:
``Notice of Intention to Adopt a Mitigated Negative Declaration.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Market Thyself: An ad in the ``Miscellaneous'' classified
section of the New York Review of Books carries only the author's
signature and the URL of her Web site:  &LR; www.annerice.com. &LR; 
Meanwhile,  &UR; J. Wingo &LR;  of  &LR; www.relationshipsearch.com &LR;  says in a
local magazine ad that he's the man to fix you up romantically,
because ``he has been there _ long marriage, late divorce and
restarting the dating game. No ivory tower here. Just practical
experience.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Self magazine shares a series of brain exercises to ``keep you
sharp for decades,'' including reading a book in the mirror. ``If
that makes you nauseated (it might), wear your watch upside down.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Bay Gelldawg &LR;  bought a copy of Universal Music's CD ``Stars
Sing Rodgers &AMP; Hart'' (you haven't lived until you've heard the
Supremes sing ``Falling in Love With Love'') and discovered that
the picture on the album cover is of Rodgers and Hammerstein.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Takedown,'' the TV movie whose San Francisco screening was
presided over by  &UR; Tina Brown &LR;  recently, has nothing to do with Talk
magazine and is wholly a Miramax undertaking, says Talk.
