<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, MAY 9
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-JAPAN-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Saturday, May 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, May 6,
about recent changes in Japanese politics misidentified the former
prime minister whose longtime political aide, Shigezo Hayasaka,
commented on the changes. He served under Kakuei Tanaka, not Noboru
Takeshita.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SIERRA-LEONE-U.N.-NYT (moved on Friday, May 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, May 5,
about the conflict in Sierra Leone between rebels and United
Nations peacekeeepers misspelled the surname of the United Nations'
spokesman at one point. He is Fred Eckhard, not Eckhart.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INDONESIA-INTERNET-NYT (moved on Monday, May 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 1,
about the efforts of an Indonesian entrepreneur to help revive his
family's fortunes misstated the location of an Internet trade show
that begins June 28. It will be at the Jakarta Convention Center,
not at the Kemayoran development site.
</P>
