<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; SCHWAB _  &LR;  At Charles Schwab &AMP; Co., ``advice'' used to be a dirty
word. The leading discount broker's original, self-imposed mandate
was to provide bare-bones securities trading at a bargain price _
period.  &UR; BY ARTHUR M. LOUIS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; MONEYBAG (COLUMN) _  &LR; Q: Our investment club has been using the
Value Line Investment Survey as a research resource. The
subscription is up for renewal, and we wonder whether there is a
different survey, weekly newsletter, or whatever, that you would
recommend.  &UR; COLUMN BY ARTHUR M. LOUIS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; JOCKS _  &LR; These days, it's easy for sports fans to get ``up close
and personal'' with their favorite athletes on the Web. Quarterback
Steve Young of the San Francisco 49ers, for example, shared
exclusive details and photos on his Web site from his
invitation-only wedding in March in Hawaii. Young said his wedding
reception was ``like a fairy tale.''  &UR; BY BENNY EVANGELISTA &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; EXCITE _  &LR;  ExciteAtHome, whose stock has fallen 59 percent this
year, is also suffering a brain drain. At least three senior
executives have left the Redwood City, Calif., Internet company in
recent weeks, and at least one more is rumored to have a foot out
the door.  &UR; BY TODD WALLACK &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; NETWORTH (COLUMN)_  &LR; The U.S. government's inflation savings bonds
haven't gotten much attention since they were introduced in
September 1998, but that may change soon.  &UR; COLUMN BY KATHLEEN &LR; 
 &UR; PENDER &LR;
